div.p:
Of their Apples they make Syder;
of their Pears, Perry; and of
their Grapes, Wine.

They have great ſtore of wilde Beaſts, as Lyons, Bears, Leopards, Tygers, Wolves, and Dogs like
Wolves, but brake not;
Virginia well ſtored with Beaſts, & Tame Cattle. Buffeloes, Elks, whoſe Fleſh is as good as Beef; Roſconnes, Utchunquois, Deer, Hares, Bevers, Ottors, Foxes, Martins, Poulcats, Weſells, Musk-Rats, Flying Squirils, &c. And for Tame Cattle, Cowes, Sheep, Goats, Hoggs, and Horſes in great plenty.
